	   <a name=97114263311218></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f97114263311218><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=7&mid=97114263311218>Creating your Cleric: Race</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=7&mid=97114263311218#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=607><span id=Sage>Gedran</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>99 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Oct 9th 9:50 PM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[4.10]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Of all the races of Norrath, only 7 can be clerics. Dark elves, High elves, Humans, Dwarves, <br>Gnomes, Erudites, and Halflings. Each type, has there own racial abilities that add to how well the cleric can be played. <br>-DE's have ultravision as well as hide which can be useful. They are also the only true evil race for clerics.<br>-High elves have the highest wisdom for more mana, as well as infravision, making them my favorite for this class. <br>-Humans are blind as bats but they don't have an EXP penalty like most races making it easier to level.<br>-Dwarves are probably the other best class for clerics, while they don't have as much wisdom, they make up for it in str and stamina. And they now also have great smithy skills to take up your extra time.<br>-Gnomes, like Dwarves, have infravison, but not too much wisdom, they make up for it in dex and agi, but those don't really come in handy. <br>-Erudites have the second most wisdom, but like Humans, they can't see at all.&nbsp;&nbsp;However it should be said for the human type clerics (Humans/Erudites) that depending on your diety selection you will be able to get some good items that offset some of the penalties.<br>-Halflings also come with the ability to hide and have infravision. They also have a slight EXP bonus which helps any Halfling lvl slightly faster.<br>If you are making an evil cleric, probably you would want to pick a DE, Erudites, might be a good choice, gnomes don't really get much guild support or much of anything, and most of the special quests come from Neriak anyway.  Also<br>Of the lighter races, High elves and Dwarves make the best clerics. They have nice starting areas, and many quests availible to them. They are also in a well populated area which gives them an advantage of saftey, and people to group with. <br>Humans and gnomes, are the runts. Halflings, Erudites, and DE's are slightly better, and they all have a few good bonuses, but are pretty much inferior to High Elves and Dwarves.<br>Gedran<br><br>Note: This is a slightly changed repost of a hugely responded previous post one or two pages back.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
