	   <tr><td colspan=2>Every class has its down side, and you have highlight some of the major ones. Every time I group I am casting heals, buffing, medding up my mana, throwing stuns, and keeping track of battle. This is most certain not the class for the stingy indivual. I give, give, and give some more, and sometimes I give so much it costs me my life.<br><br>On the upside I rarely have problem getting into a good group. My friends list is completely full ( By the way Verant can you please make that darn thing longer! )and when I do log on I have one person or another telling me to come and party with them. <br><br>Even though Druids and Shaman get many of our healing spells, they must wait one circle later. They are not awarded Superior Healing until until level 53 ( We get it at lvl 34 ). The healing spell Complete Heal is ours and ours alone, which you will get at level 39.<br><br>The point on the quest armor is well taken. The gold armor is questionable at best, and the waiting for the items is a pain in the rear. But be happy that as a Cleric there is not much armor out there that you cant wear. In terms of low level quests I think you need to look again. Plenty of low level items out there. Even a few really good one's depending on your race/diety.<br><br>As for being poor, it sucks. We are all poor when we start out, and Clerics get it the worst. But it does get better, just hang in there. At level 11 you are still going through the worst of it.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
