	   <tr><td colspan=2>Well, at the bottom of my spaces has been and always will be Divine Aura.....That is consant from Lv 1. Ill say what i had at lvl 25 since that is what most of you are commentating on. <br>I always keep my nuke up in first slot, as that is just common sense...you need self defence.<br>You want to keep two heals memed as it was said earlier, the best heal is for tanks, second one is for casters. After that keep root and stuns memed......they will help you and if you have plenty of mana, you can stun the mob and save the tanks for a sec which will save you mana later on. Gate is optionable....If your in a dungeon keep it memed, if not save the space. That leaves one or two spots open. Dont keep buffs in there, they can be memed as tanks need them. with your spare slot, keep what ever you need....an additional stun, invigor, what ever is handy. <br><br>Incase you care, at lvl 39 i keep (from top to bottom) Wrath, Sheal, Gheal, enstill, force, atone, Divine barrier, Divine aura. Thats all from me.<br><br>Yuuno Nanataku<br>39 cleric<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
