	   <tr><td colspan=2>I've been in Eruds Crossing for the last 3 lvls, made good exp but mostly a lot of money.&nbsp;&nbsp;I still have 130pp, after all my spells and some additional Banded & Bronze armor on me.<br><br>But here came the catch..  I also have a lvl 16 warrior, but found out... that the cleric can't work as well, in the same areas.  So I went to HighPass.  Well, lvl 15 is a bit too low.  Did grouped, but barely got any experience cause every one was lvl 17-19.  Last night, place was overcrowed.  No responce for groups.  Went to Oasis, and got a response right away... and probably lead to my best experience yet.<br><br>For the 90 minutes I was in Oasis, this group became more daring the moment I joined in.   Well, I got a few scare when I didn't know if I could keep them alive.  I did!  Not mentioning a lag on the spells I cast, I barely saved our enchanter with 1/2 a bub left.  Then our druid... the warrior..  over and over again.  We had 3 Ghouls and a Dry bone skels on us once.  All caster got oom, but we did make it.  That's when I finally felt like I earned my spot in this group.  And I think they saw how good a cleric can be in the group.  The moment I left, 5 minutes later they were doing shouts looking for a cleric.  Made me smile, there are people out there that can use us... hehe<br><br>Well, enough with that story.  I want to make sure I'm wanted, so other than Oasis... where is a good place for my Cleric to go ?  I hate wasting an hour of my night trying to find a location for groups...  So if I know the good areas, it will save me some time.<br><br>Thanks.<br><br>SoulSavor<br>High elf  15th Cleric<br>Lanys T'Vyl<br><br>Thornan<br>Barbarian 16th Warrior<br>Lanys T'Vyl<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
