	   <tr><td colspan=2>We get three lines of buffs.&nbsp;&nbsp;The first, CourageValorResolutionHeroism, is HP/AC; the second, the shield line, which you keep referring to as the blessing (makes my teeth curl, I'm afraid) is just AC; the third, the Symbol line, is just HP.  I do my damnedest to keep all three on everyone in my party.  (Rarely, on such things as planes raids, our party isn't taking damage and I might not cast Symbol of Marzin on my party, at 11pp per buff.  I discuss this with them, though.)<br><br>Please remember -- that mana-guzzling AC buff is the equivalent of another breastplate or shield.  Do you think if you asked any of your partymembers if they would like a second shield to hold in an imaginary third hand, they would decline the offer?  You may think it's trivial, those extra 29 points to their AC; they don't.<br>&nbsp;<br>Ismena, 65 Cleric<br>Prexus<br>That's =Doctor= Barbie to you</td></tr>
