	   <tr><td colspan=2>First off, on the spells, that's a pretty good line up, although if you have a nuker or 2 druids/shamans in your party don't bother with furor, the 19max damage is not worth the waste of mana on a death beetle, and the 41max damage from ward undead, and 80+ from expulse helps enormously, are much more efficiant and effective on everything else.&nbsp;&nbsp;Healing of course, needs not to be mentioned, as well as divine aura which has saved me from NUMEROUS trains.  Root can be used at your discretion, snare is much better, as well as Yalup since a 18 seconds of str won't do much from lvl's 1-18.  Stun again, is a life saver, not only does it interrupt casting, it also reduces the damage taken over a short period of time, by your tanks.  Spook the dead however, is absolute stupidity, Just by the fact that one wrong cast can pull every last piece of yard trash, and anything heading back to the house on you.  And if you are retreating, root is much better since it won't chase you, nor will it aggro other mobs on you.  Instead, a memed cure disease (if fighting mummies) or a buff of some kind would be better.<br><br>The rest of this posting is very good advice, pulling away from the house, and spawn areas can save you from having to deal with extra yard trash or trains, as well as rooting and stunning, which keep the mobs occupied and ready to be killed.<br>Gedran<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
